          <msContents>
            <summary>[p]Calendarium. Containing Festa mobilia, Tabula planetarum, Homo venarum, Tabula lunae. 
[p]Written in red and black in a neat gothic script. Initials in alternate red and blue for the Vein section and the Moon tables. 
[p]There is a rough outline pendrawing in red of a male figure to illustrate the 'Homo venarum'. 
[p]Title in alternate red and black: 'Indictiones/ffesta mobilia/Tabula planetarum/Homo venarum/Tabula lune'.</summary>
            <textLang mainLang="" source="IANA">Latin</textLang>
            <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_39_1">
              <author/>
              <title type="original">Single leaf from a folding almanac, second half of the fifteenth century, including calendar information and medical summaries</title>
              <title type="standard"/>
              <textLang mainLang="" source="IANA">Latin</textLang>
              <filiation/>
